al Visualization  What to Expect      What to Expect  Please Note : Upon approval of our revised curriculum proposal later this academic year, the MS in Biomedical Visualization program will begin classes for newly admitted students on 6/15/2020, instead of 8/24/2020, as previously scheduled.  Thinking about joining our program? Find out what you can expect as a student at UIC.       Year 1    Year 1    Year 2         Fall    Spring    Summer       Everyone begins the semester with three days of orientation the week before classes begin with a day of introductions, tours, administrative, and informational sessions. During orientation, our new students attend a full day workshop presented by Vitruvian Studio , where they work with artists Melinda Whitmore and David Jamison to create a scale écorché figure before beginning the gross anatomy course.   Required courses        ANAT 441  Gross Human Anatomy  5 hours    BHIS 499  Information Sources in BHIS  1 hour    BVIS 505  Visual Learning & Visual Thinking I  2 hours    BVIS 510  Anatomical Visualization  3 hours    BVIS 595  Seminar in BVIS  1 hour      Electives        BVIS 500  Biomedical Visualization Techniques  1 hours      Opportunities   Join the Student Association of Medical Artists (SAMA) at UIC  Register as an AMI Student Member      Resources       UIC Library of the Health Sciences   Use the BVIS Research Guide for resources to support your study in anatomy and research-related work         BVIS student blog   The blog that all BVIS students share to highlight  work and activities            You’ll begin your research in the spring by selecting topics and research advisors. Courses in illustration, design, modeling and animation provide you with a solid foundation in visual problem solving and critical thinking.   Required courses        BHIS 500  Strategic Inquiry in BHIS (first 8 weeks)  3 hours    BVIS 552  Graphic Design  2 hours    BVIS 597  Project Research (last 8 weeks)  1 hour      Electives        BVIS 519  Modeling I  3 hours    BVIS 522  Illustration Techniques  3 hours    BVIS 541  Animation I  2 hours    BVIS 596  Independent Study  1-4 hours     At least one of these courses:        ANAT 403  Human Neuroanatomy (first 8 weeks)  3 hours    ANAT 544  Advanced Craniofacial Anatomy  3 hours    BVIS 560  Molecular Pharmacology  3 hours      Opportunities   Register for the AMI Annual Conference in July and consider being an onsite student volunteer to defray some cost of your student registration  Enter the AMI Student Salon        BVIS summer moves fast with most students attending the AMI Annual Conference later in July. Research presentations in BHIS 595 seminar are a highlight of the summer as you’ll complete your research proposal.   Required courses        BHIS 405  Medical Sciences and Human Pathophysiology  3 hours    BHIS 595  Seminar in BHIS  1 hour    BVIS 518  Web Development  2 hours      Electives             BVIS 520  Modeling II  3 hours    BVIS 535  Visual Learning & Visual Thinking II  2 hours    BVIS 538  Medical Legal Visualization  2 hours    BVIS 542  Animation II  3 hours    BVIS 596  Independent Study  1-4 hours                AMI Annual Conference July 25-29, 2019 Milwaukee, WI  The AMI annual meeting is a gathering of professional, student, and associate members of our association. Three days of plenary and concurrent sessions cover a rich variety of topics including art and visualization, biomedical subjects and business practices.   Register            Fall    Spring       Students agree that the Clinical Sciences course is the highlight of the semester! You’ll complete rotations through various medical specialty departments, looking over shoulders of celebrated UIC physicians and surgeons.   Required courses        BVIS 502  Clinical Sciences for BVIS  3 hours    BVIS 597  Project Research  1-3 hours      At least one of these courses        GEMS 501  Biochemistry  3 hours    GEMS 502  Molecular Biology  3 hours    GEMS 503  Cell Biology  3 hours    NEUS 501  Foundations of Neuroscience I  3 hours      Electives        ART 454  3D Space I: Modeling (Maya)  4 hours    BVIS 543  Animation III  4 hours    BVIS 548  Advanced Illustration Techniques  3 hours    BVIS 562  Advanced Graphic Design  3 hours    BVIS 580  Practicum in BVIS  6-12 hours    BVIS 523  Haptics I  2 hours    BVIS 536  Interactive Visualization  3 hours    BVIS 596  Independent Study  1-4 hours      Opportunities       Apply   Apply for Vesalius Trust Scholarships         Present   Present a research poster during Applied Health Sciences Research Day         Enter   Enter the NSF and Popular Science Vizzies            Look forward to the completion and presentation of your research! You’ll prepare for professional life after graduate school by gaining valuable insight into business practices and exploring the unique and diverse employment opportunities for which you’ve been prepared.   Required courses        BVIS 575  Business Practices  3 hours    BVIS 597  Project Research  1-2 hours      Electives        ART 455  3D Space II: Animation (Maya)  4 hours    BVIS 530  Surgical Illustration  4 hours    BVIS 544  Animation IV  4 hours    BVIS 580  Practicum in BVIS  6-12 hours    BVIS 521  Modeling III  2 hours    BVIS 537  Advanced Interactive Visualization  3 hours    BVIS 537  Special Topics in 360 degree Animation  2 hours    BVIS 596  Independent Study  1-4 hours    GEMS 515  Receptor Pharmacology and Cell Signaling  Prereq: GCLS 501 Biochemistry or approval of the dept.  3 hours    NEUS 502  Foundations of Neuroscience II  3 hours      Opportunities   Enter UIC’s Student Research Forum  Enter UIC Image of Research Competition – Deadline usually in late June  Register for the Association of Medical Illustrators Annual Conference in July and consider being an onsite student volunteer to defray some cost of your student registration  Enter the AMI Student Salon  Enter BioCommunications Association Bioimages 2017  Upon graduation complete your application for Professional Member status and a free year of membership in the Association of Medical Illustrators. Request a sponsor letter from a Certified Medical Illustrator such as a BVIS faculty member. Apply here »            Biomedical and Health Information Sciences    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          BS in Health Information Management    Expand BS in Health Information Management menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      Minor in Life Science Visualization    Expand Minor in Life Science Visualization menu          What to Expect    Applying      MS in Biomedical Visualization    Expand MS in Biomedical Visualization menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Meet Our Students    Expand Meet Our Students menu          Class of 2020    Class of 2021        MS in Health Informatics    PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics    Expand PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty      Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Information Management    Post-Master’s Certificate in Health Informatics    Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Informatics      News    Calendar    Directory    Contact                College of  Applied Health  Sciences       UI Health Logo                            Quick Links    Calendar    Directory    News    Inside AHS    Graduation      Resources    Academic Support and Achievement Program    Student Resources    Faculty and Staff Resources    Academic Calendar      Tools    myUIC    GoogleApps@UIC    Webmail    Blackboard    Nessie        Connect with AHS    Contact us    Apply Now    Give to AHS         1919 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60612  312-996-6695  ahsinfo@uic.edu    Social Media Accou